  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At this point, we have arrived in Nice, where there were consuls and consulates.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the aim for my brother and myself was to get to Portugal and then to England, also hoping my uncle and aunt would be able to get to Portugal and perhaps get into England, although that was very dicey, as they were not either a child or a father.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the English-- there was a war on, and they only allowed children of refugees or parents of refugees.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We applied for a Spanish visa because, as I said, they wouldn't allow me to cross the Pyrenees, because I was too young.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we went regularly to the Spanish consulate to see whether our visa, our transit visa, had arrived and we were always told, no, no, no.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Eventually, after about four months, I arrived one morning with my brother and in the book of names, I saw the name Robinson.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I said to him, well, that's us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That's Rubinstein.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I wasn't lying.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "For one moment, I saw the R and I thought it was us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He stamped our passport and I'll never know whether he was [INAUDIBLE] or couldn't read, or whether he was sorry for us, or whether we'd nagged him long enough, but anyway that day we were given a transit visa to-- transit visa to Spain and Portugal.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In our status-- on our-- on our name status paper.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] what also helped us to get a Spanish visa was the fact that the Jews were advised, if they could afford it in Belgium, to buy entry visas to places like Puerto Rico, Costa Rica, Cuba, Mexico.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we actually purchased a visa-- or my uncle purchased a visa-- to Bolivia, a [INAUDIBLE] which is there.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
